To make a Bootstrap table sortable alphanumerically by clicking the headers without using jQuery or other plugins, you can use JavaScript to achieve this. Here's a simple example of how you can do it:

HTML:
```html
<table id="sortable-table" class="table table-striped">
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th onclick="sortTable(0)">Column 1</th>
      <th onclick="sortTable(1)">Column 2</th>
      <!-- Add more columns as needed -->
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td>Row 1, Column 1</td>
