- The median is the middle value of the dataset when it is sorted in order. It is a robust measure, meaning it is not affected by outliers. It is usually calculated using either sorting the dataset and counting from the sorted list or using an existing algorithm like the Powell method.
- The mode is the most frequent value in the dataset. This measure is useful in categorical data analysis, where the data is categorized into a few discrete values. Unlike the mean and median, it cannot be easily computed for continuous data.

