To make a POST request in TypeScript sending a file, you can use the FormData object in combination with the fetch API. Here's an example of how to do it:

```typescript
let formData = new FormData();
formData.append('param1', 'value1');
formData.append('param2', 'value2');
formData.append('file', fileData, file.name);
let request = new Request('https://example.com/upload', {
    method: 'POST',
    body: formData
});
fetch(request)
   .then(response => response.text())
   .then(result => console.log(result))
   .catch(error => console.error(error));
```

In this example, formData is an instance of FormData, which can be used to add key/value pairs or files to the request body. You can add multiple files by using the append() method multiple times, with the file data as the second parameter and the file name as the third parameter. In this example, we add three parameters ('param1', 'value1'), ('param2', 'value2'), and ('file', fileData, file.name), where fileData is the file data itself and file is the file object representing the file to be uploaded.

